JOHANNESBURG - Exclusive Books chief executive, Benjamin Trisk has left the bookstore's board on Wednesday according to reports by BusinessDay. READ: SACP slams SSA for trying to censor Jacques Pauw book Trisk reportedly reached an "amicable settlement" with the board and confirmed the company was profitable when he left. Exclusive Books chairperson, Mark Barnes acknowledged Trisk's sizeable contribution to the “re-engineering of the Exclusive Books business and brand” in a statement. The news of Trisk's suspension emerged in February but reasons for the rift remain murky. Trisk stated he was "astonished" by the reasons given in the suspension letter he received. eNCA